New Records: Ireland achieved their second win over South Africa in ODIs.
Paul Stirling and Andy Balbirnie formed their second-highest partnership for Ireland against South Africa.
Harry Tector scored his first half-century in ODIs.
Key Match Events: Major performances included Paul Stirling and Andy Balbirnie's partnership, Harry Tector's half-century, and the quick dismissal of South Africa's top order.
Turning points included South Africa's struggles under lights and Ireland's effective bowling.
Pre-Game Insights: Ireland won the toss and made the most of favorable conditions; South Africa's top batters were dismissed early, and the new ball swung more under lights.
Post-Match Reflections: Players and coaches reacted positively to the win, which was a morale booster; Ireland's resilience was noted, and there were no immediate announcements of retirements.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The weather and pitch conditions affected play, with swing being a factor; Ireland's performance under lights was a contrast to previous games.
